<org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription xmi:version="2.0" xmlns:xmi="http://www.omg.org/XMI" xmlns:org.eclipse.epf.uma="http://www.eclipse.org/epf/uma/1.0.6/uma.ecore" xmlns:epf="http://www.eclipse.org/epf" epf:version="1.5.1" xmi:id="-MagTtdA6aC-CTjyQ4ah6ng" name=",_iuLOUCzHEeKtGPioRDeGQg" guid="-MagTtdA6aC-CTjyQ4ah6ng" changeDate="2012-11-12T14:00:04.535+0100">
  <mainDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    In the networked enterprise there is a need to support a shared work space or group where users of network partners can&#xD;
    collaborate with each other. These groups can be formal and informal on-demand groups / spaces.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The Innovation Community of the NEFFICS Platform supports three kinds of groups, as well as access control and&#xD;
    categorization. The group kinds are:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Standard group&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Support forum&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Group linked to focus area&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul></mainDescription>
  <purpose>&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        To create appropriate working groups in the NEFFICS Innovation Community.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul></purpose>
</org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription>
